  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nBecause the genesis of the medalla testnet has not started yet, the validator client writes an error message to the console. This irritated me because I assumed that something is set up the wrong way.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nBranch: `master` (Lighthouse 0.1.2-a37e75f4)\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently, the `lighthouse validator_client` expects a running beacon chain node. \r\nBecause the beacon chain node started with `lighthouse beacon_node --eth1 --http` is currently `Waiting for more deposits`,\r\nthis results in the following error message of the `lighthouse validator_client`:\r\n```bash\r\nUnable to connect to beacon node        error: \"ReqwestError(reqwest::Error { kind: Request, url: \\\"http://localhost:5052/node/version\\\", source: hyper::Error(Connect, ConnectError(\\\"tcp connect error\\\", Os { code: 111, kind: ConnectionRefused, message: \\\"Connection refused\\\" })) })\"\r\n```\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nI would expect an info instead of an error message saying something like \r\n`INFO Waiting for genesis.`\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the number of active validators could be displayed.",
